WEBVTT

00:01.830 --> 00:04.540
[ Humming ]

00:04.540 --> 00:06.920
I've never seen her
this happy.

00:06.920 --> 00:10.000
I have, but only in pictures
from before we were born.

00:10.000 --> 00:12.040
My guess is that
she's gone insane.

00:12.040 --> 00:13.380
I know
we've thought that before,

00:13.380 --> 00:15.120
but it seems real
this time.

00:15.120 --> 00:17.540
Very creative, Anna-Kat,
but wrong.

00:17.540 --> 00:19.880
I'm just enjoying
my new lasagna business.

00:19.880 --> 00:22.750
Best decision
I ever made.

00:22.750 --> 00:24.420
I have
seven steady customers,

00:24.420 --> 00:27.000
and my boss -- me --
is a delight.

00:28.960 --> 00:30.420
Is that
how you package it?

00:30.420 --> 00:32.250
Don't you know
presentation is everything?

00:32.250 --> 00:34.960
Oliver, sweetie, I'm gonna
invite you to shut up.

00:37.290 --> 00:39.290
Franklin.
What are you doing here?

00:39.290 --> 00:40.540
I'm spending the weekend.

00:40.540 --> 00:42.880
My mom's at a church retreat
in Atlantic City.

00:42.880 --> 00:44.750
They're going to improve
the church's finances

00:44.750 --> 00:46.210
through the blessings
of card counting.

00:46.210 --> 00:47.920
Huh.

00:47.920 --> 00:50.330
I don't remember
talking to her about that.

00:50.330 --> 00:52.290
Anna-Kat thought it
would be better if we
just sprung it on you.

00:53.580 --> 00:54.750
You always say
it's easier

00:54.750 --> 00:56.620
to ask for forgiveness
than permission.

00:56.620 --> 00:59.040
Anna-Kat,
Mommy doesn't like it

00:59.040 --> 01:01.000
when you use her words
against her.

01:01.000 --> 01:02.710
I've got $50
I'm supposed to give

01:02.710 --> 01:04.710
to whoever watches me.

01:04.710 --> 01:06.420
I'll watch him for $50.

01:06.420 --> 01:08.420
I can cross
number 37 off

01:08.420 --> 01:10.460
that stupid life-skills list
you're forcing me to do --

01:10.460 --> 01:11.710
"Get and keep a job."

01:11.710 --> 01:13.330
Okay.

01:13.330 --> 01:14.960
Why don't you take
Anna-Kat and Franklin upstairs

01:14.960 --> 01:16.290
and get him unpacked?

01:16.290 --> 01:18.210
I could use a hand
with my luggage.

01:18.210 --> 01:19.620
Isn't that
your luggage?

01:19.620 --> 01:22.210
Hilarious.
No, that's my carry-on.

01:24.620 --> 01:27.380
I couldn't help but notice
you called this a "business."

01:27.380 --> 01:29.790
I have clients.
It's a business.

01:29.790 --> 01:31.420
Is it?
Yes!

01:31.420 --> 01:32.540
Prove it.

01:32.540 --> 01:34.540
You love "Shark Tank."
Let me "Shark Tank" you.

01:34.540 --> 01:35.880
Fine.

01:35.880 --> 01:37.120
Let's do this.

01:39.750 --> 01:41.710
Okay, hit me
with your pitch.

01:41.710 --> 01:44.040
"Mama's Zazagna"
is the best thing

01:44.040 --> 01:46.500
to hit the Westport food scene
in years.

01:46.500 --> 01:47.960
Don't love the name.

01:47.960 --> 01:50.170
It's what Anna-Kat used to
call it when she was young.

01:50.170 --> 01:51.830
She also used to
bark at the mailman,

01:51.830 --> 01:53.330
so not everything she did
was so great.

01:53.330 --> 01:54.880
But continue.

01:54.880 --> 01:57.830
The poor starving husbands
of Westport are flocking to me.

01:57.830 --> 01:59.500
In the three weeks
that I've been in business,

01:59.500 --> 02:02.210
I have sold 120 servings.

02:02.210 --> 02:03.960
And what is
the price per unit?

02:03.960 --> 02:05.540
$5 a pop.

02:05.540 --> 02:07.120
And how much have you invested
in the business?

02:07.120 --> 02:08.580
Let's see.

02:08.580 --> 02:11.330
Ingredients,
containers...

02:11.330 --> 02:14.420
$473.17.

02:14.420 --> 02:15.290
[ Door opens ]

02:18.750 --> 02:19.750
[ Door closes ]

02:19.750 --> 02:21.790
I like
to have choices.

02:21.790 --> 02:25.500
Okay, $600 in gross
minus your investment...

02:25.500 --> 02:27.330
Factor in the three lasagnas
you burned last week

02:27.330 --> 02:29.830
when you got distracted
by "90 Day Fiancé"...

02:29.830 --> 02:33.960
Mama's Zazagna has made
roughly $11.28.

02:33.960 --> 02:36.210
No.
That can't be right.

02:36.210 --> 02:38.080
Listen,
Katie, was it?

02:38.080 --> 02:39.460
Your lasagna is great.

02:39.460 --> 02:42.420
But this isn't a business.
It's a hobby.

02:42.420 --> 02:44.710
You're not an entrepreneur.
You're a want-repreneur.

02:44.710 --> 02:46.670
And for that reason,
I'm out.

02:46.670 --> 02:51.540
♪♪

02:51.540 --> 02:55.290
♪♪

02:55.290 --> 02:56.500
Ah, damn it,
Katie,

02:56.500 --> 02:58.830
why is this stupid lasagna
so delicious?

02:58.830 --> 03:01.330
Now that I'm getting divorced,
I shouldn't be exposed to this!

03:01.330 --> 03:03.040
I don't know.
Why don't you mix it up?

03:03.040 --> 03:04.500
Fat Doris could be fun.

03:04.500 --> 03:07.210
You'd get some cleavage,
grow into your glasses.

03:07.210 --> 03:09.380
Oliver did
this stupid thing

03:09.380 --> 03:12.620
where he took my profits
and deducted what I spent.

03:12.620 --> 03:15.380
Turns out I'm making
17 cents an hour.

03:15.380 --> 03:17.210
Mm, I don't know
if you can blame that on him.

03:17.210 --> 03:18.460
Oliver is
good at business.

03:18.460 --> 03:20.040
Maybe he can help you.
You're right.

03:20.040 --> 03:21.460
It'd be nice to get
something out of him

03:21.460 --> 03:22.960
besides a dirty look
every time I tell him

03:22.960 --> 03:24.540
I won't pay
for his dry cleaning.

03:24.540 --> 03:26.250
Speaking of
business opportunities,

03:26.250 --> 03:27.540
I've been working
on contracts

03:27.540 --> 03:30.250
for this 20-something
YouTube star, Lonnie Spears,

03:30.250 --> 03:32.330
and he's looking for
a ghostwriter for his memoirs.

03:32.330 --> 03:33.830
Any interest, Greg?

03:33.830 --> 03:35.290
Thank you, Angela,

03:35.290 --> 03:37.210
but I'll stick to writing
important historical books.

03:37.210 --> 03:39.830
Oh. Are you working
on something new?

03:39.830 --> 03:42.540
Actually, I'm working
on something old.

03:43.830 --> 03:45.920
That's a bit
of historical humor.

03:45.920 --> 03:47.960
[ Chuckling ] It killed
in the faculty lounge.

03:50.040 --> 03:51.170
I'll see myself out.

03:51.170 --> 03:57.960
♪♪

04:02.790 --> 04:03.880
[ Door opens ]

04:04.710 --> 04:06.120
Hi, Mr. Otto.

04:06.120 --> 04:07.580
Taylor and Anna-Kat
are making snacks.

04:07.580 --> 04:09.790
I thought I'd come in
for a little guy time.

04:09.790 --> 04:10.960
Now's not good.

04:10.960 --> 04:12.120
You having a hard time
with the writing?

04:12.120 --> 04:13.540
Franklin, I --

04:13.540 --> 04:14.790
You don't have to
hide anything from me.

04:14.790 --> 04:16.710
I came in here earlier
and checked out your computer.

04:16.710 --> 04:18.040
I'm a snooper.

04:18.040 --> 04:19.880
Well, your snack's
probably ready, so...

04:19.880 --> 04:21.330
I don't know why you don't
want to write that book

04:21.330 --> 04:22.500
for the YouTube guy.

04:22.500 --> 04:24.380
That's not
really your business.

04:24.380 --> 04:26.290
Your wife
is bettering herself,

04:26.290 --> 04:28.290
you're asking your daughter
to better herself,

04:28.290 --> 04:30.000
but you just want to stay
right where you are.

04:32.330 --> 04:34.040
Is this candy or a rock?

04:35.040 --> 04:36.170
Rock.

04:37.880 --> 04:39.290
You're right, Franklin.

04:39.290 --> 04:40.500
I have to
get out of my comfort zone.

04:40.500 --> 04:41.670
Okay.

04:41.670 --> 04:43.000
While I was
in here earlier,

04:43.000 --> 04:45.290
I took the liberty of buying you
some fruit trees online.

04:45.290 --> 04:47.040
You'll thank me
in the spring.

04:49.250 --> 04:51.210
[ Sighs ]

04:51.210 --> 04:52.920
I have been thinking

04:52.920 --> 04:54.880
about our conversation
this morning.

04:54.880 --> 04:56.670
I knew you'd come to me.

04:56.670 --> 04:58.580
I'm impressed you can admit
you're out of your depth.

04:58.580 --> 05:00.620
Having
some other thoughts now.

05:00.620 --> 05:02.830
I'm not doing this
out of the goodness of my heart.

05:02.830 --> 05:04.670
No one thinks that.

05:04.670 --> 05:06.380
Running a small business
will look good

05:06.380 --> 05:08.620
on my Harvard application,
along with Teen Help Line.

05:08.620 --> 05:10.750
But if we do this, I'm gonna
need a financial stake.

05:10.750 --> 05:12.000
How about 10%?

05:12.000 --> 05:14.080
I will not work
for anything less than 50.

05:14.080 --> 05:15.460
I will call
your girlfriend's parents

05:15.460 --> 05:16.580
and invite them
over for dinner.

05:16.580 --> 05:17.710
10% is fine.

05:17.710 --> 05:18.920
♪♪

05:22.620 --> 05:24.750
♪♪

05:24.750 --> 05:25.920
What are these?

05:25.920 --> 05:27.830
Labels for our product.

05:27.830 --> 05:30.540
What the hell is
"Coastal Farms Lasagna"?

05:30.540 --> 05:33.750
Our new name. It's perfect.
It sounds fancy and healthy.

05:33.750 --> 05:35.620
I don't like it.
Change it back.

05:35.620 --> 05:36.920
Can't.

05:36.920 --> 05:38.080
I already submitted
an application

05:38.080 --> 05:39.710
to Flavor of Westport
under the new name.

05:39.710 --> 05:41.540
Oliver, you can't
just change things

05:41.540 --> 05:42.880
without consulting me.

05:42.880 --> 05:44.380
You asked for my help.

05:44.380 --> 05:46.500
Flavor of Westport is key
to growing our business.

05:46.500 --> 05:48.120
That's where
all the restaurants in town

05:48.120 --> 05:50.460
give out samples of their food
to bring in new customers.

05:50.460 --> 05:52.290
We do well there,
we're on our way.

05:52.290 --> 05:54.080
No offense, but you slap
the noodles and cheese together.

05:54.080 --> 05:55.880
Let me do the thinking.

05:55.880 --> 05:57.710
Saying "No offense" doesn't
make it any less offensive.

05:57.710 --> 05:59.080
Here, let me try.

05:59.080 --> 06:00.670
No offense,

06:00.670 --> 06:02.000
but you have the arms
of an American Girl Doll.

06:02.880 --> 06:04.460
I said "No offense."

06:04.460 --> 06:11.170
♪♪

06:11.170 --> 06:12.710
Franklin:
The antelopes are so cute.

06:12.710 --> 06:16.000
Aww! The baby's
having trouble keeping up.

06:16.000 --> 06:17.420
Don't get
emotionally invested

06:17.420 --> 06:19.500
in the slow-moving antelopes,
Franklin.

06:19.500 --> 06:21.460
Babysitting is
a piece of cake.

06:21.460 --> 06:23.380
They haven't moved
in two hours.

06:23.380 --> 06:24.710
Has it been two hours?

06:24.710 --> 06:26.250
Because I haven't
stopped eating cereal.

06:27.580 --> 06:28.920
That's a lot of cereal.

06:28.920 --> 06:30.420
Hey, guys.
Guess what.

06:30.420 --> 06:31.830
I have a meeting
with Lonnie Spears today.

06:31.830 --> 06:33.080
No way!

06:33.080 --> 06:33.880
He's looking
for a ghostwriter.

06:33.880 --> 06:35.330
[ Gasps ]

06:35.330 --> 06:37.330
Before you go there,
neither of us are ghosts.

06:37.330 --> 06:38.960
[ Sighs ]

06:38.960 --> 06:40.710
But I don't know
the first thing about him.

06:40.710 --> 06:42.460
Oh, he does
these hilarious pranks online.

06:42.460 --> 06:43.500
Look.

06:46.620 --> 06:49.080
Shh.

06:49.080 --> 06:50.460
Lonnie! No!
[ Laughs ]

06:50.460 --> 06:52.380
Can't I just
take a shower?!

06:52.380 --> 06:53.670
[ Paintball gun fires ]
[ Screams ]

06:53.670 --> 06:54.960
That stings!

06:54.960 --> 06:56.500
Lonnie! I hate you!

06:57.710 --> 06:59.170
Congrats.

06:59.170 --> 07:01.580
You're now the proud owner
of a Wendy's franchise.

07:01.580 --> 07:03.620
[ Chuckles ]
Lonnie, you can't just keep
giving me restaurants.

07:03.620 --> 07:04.710
I don't know
what I'm doing.

07:04.710 --> 07:06.290
I believe in you, bro!

07:06.290 --> 07:07.500
Lonnie --
[ Exhales sharply ]

07:07.500 --> 07:09.580
[ Voice breaking ]
I love you!

07:09.580 --> 07:11.960
You know what happens
when you cry.

07:11.960 --> 07:13.330
[ Paintball gun fires ]
Ow!

07:13.330 --> 07:14.830
[ Both laugh ]

07:14.830 --> 07:15.880
He makes money
off of this?

07:15.880 --> 07:16.920
Millions.

07:16.920 --> 07:18.290
I know life isn't fair,

07:18.290 --> 07:19.540
but it seems like
it's getting worse.

07:19.540 --> 07:21.210
I'm a middle-aged
history professor.

07:21.210 --> 07:22.500
How am I supposed to
connect with this guy?

07:22.500 --> 07:23.790
You've got to
speak his language --

07:23.790 --> 07:25.080
prank him.

07:25.080 --> 07:26.920
I don't know.
I'm not much of a prankster.

07:26.920 --> 07:29.960
Although, once,
I did a hilarious one.

07:29.960 --> 07:32.000
[ Laughing ]
I put on Wikipedia

07:32.000 --> 07:35.000
that General
Peter Marshall Stevenson

07:35.000 --> 07:36.170
was born in Illinois!

07:36.170 --> 07:38.880
[ Laughing ]

07:38.880 --> 07:40.040
[ Pounds counter ]

07:40.040 --> 07:41.670
He never left Essex!

07:41.670 --> 07:43.620
[ Laughs ]

07:43.620 --> 07:45.290
Yeah, maybe something
cooler than that.

07:46.330 --> 07:47.710
He loves shooting people
with paintball guns.

07:47.710 --> 07:49.710
Just do that.
He'll totally respect it.

07:49.710 --> 07:51.080
I'm clearly
out of my element here,

07:51.080 --> 07:52.380
so I'm gonna
trust you on this.

07:52.380 --> 07:54.120
I'm having
a weird couple of days.

07:54.120 --> 07:55.210
First, I got career advice
from Franklin,

07:55.210 --> 07:56.460
and now you, Trip.

07:56.460 --> 07:58.330
I'm gonna go see
if Luthor's got anything for me.

07:58.330 --> 08:00.040
Run, baby antelope!
Run!

08:00.040 --> 08:01.500
Where are its parents?!

08:01.500 --> 08:03.960
Don't worry, that's them
crossing the river to --

08:03.960 --> 08:05.580
Oh, no! Crocodiles!

08:05.580 --> 08:07.170
This is a nightmare!

08:07.170 --> 08:11.580
♪♪

08:11.580 --> 08:13.710
Yeah, sorry to cut this short,

08:13.710 --> 08:16.330
but Flavor of Westport
is tomorrow,

08:16.330 --> 08:19.580
and to participate, you have to
own a local restaurant.

08:19.580 --> 08:21.620
You don't have one,
so I'm afraid we're done here.

08:21.620 --> 08:22.620
Oh.

08:22.620 --> 08:23.880
Hold on.

08:23.880 --> 08:26.210
I'm aware of that requirement,
but it's not an issue.

08:26.210 --> 08:28.330
In the 1770s,
there was a brothel

08:28.330 --> 08:30.380
on the land
where our house now sits.

08:30.380 --> 08:33.330
Due to a law
that dates back even further,

08:33.330 --> 08:35.830
because that brothel had
a liquor license,

08:35.830 --> 08:37.420
the Otto home does,
as well.

08:37.420 --> 08:39.670
Which legally
makes our home...

08:39.670 --> 08:41.830
a restaurant.
A restaurant.

08:41.830 --> 08:43.420
How do you know that?

08:43.420 --> 08:45.750
Dad told us that fact,
like, a million times.

08:45.750 --> 08:46.960
Every time
your father says,

08:46.960 --> 08:48.250
"Oh, this is
an interesting tidbit,"

08:48.250 --> 08:50.170
I smile, nod,
and power down.

08:50.170 --> 08:52.000
I went online
and found some copies

08:52.000 --> 08:53.080
of all the old documents.

08:54.290 --> 08:56.080
I'm impressed.

08:56.080 --> 08:57.460
Me too!

08:57.460 --> 08:58.460
Seal the deal.

09:00.330 --> 09:01.920
Try this.

09:07.380 --> 09:09.380
Delicious!

09:09.380 --> 09:11.250
And I love the name.

09:11.250 --> 09:13.250
"Coastal Farms Lasagna,"
sounds fancy.

09:14.500 --> 09:17.380
But this is
Flavor of Westport,

09:17.380 --> 09:20.170
so you'll obviously
have to change the recipe.

09:20.170 --> 09:24.380
As of this year, we are now
a healthy-choices food festival.

09:24.380 --> 09:26.750
The noodles
need to be gluten-free

09:26.750 --> 09:28.620
and you'll have to
replace the mozzarella

09:28.620 --> 09:31.250
with one of
the nut-based cheeses.

09:31.250 --> 09:34.250
Cashew, Brazil,
almond, pistachio...

09:34.250 --> 09:37.120
What nut you choose
is up to you.

09:37.120 --> 09:39.290
Of course.
No problem.

09:39.290 --> 09:41.710
"No problem"?
What are you talking about?

09:41.710 --> 09:43.000
Mom,
let me handle this.

09:43.000 --> 09:45.500
No! This is where
I draw the line!

09:45.500 --> 09:47.040
I asked you to help me
grow my business,

09:47.040 --> 09:48.880
not make this
into something else.

09:48.880 --> 09:50.380
We're not
changing the recipe

09:50.380 --> 09:52.380
just to get into
this crappy festival!

09:54.710 --> 09:56.500
I think
maybe it's best if you --

09:56.500 --> 09:58.540
Oh, you don't have to
tell me to leave, Sam.

09:58.540 --> 10:00.750
I'll just go home
and get yelled at by my mother

10:00.750 --> 10:02.380
in our historic whorehouse.

10:02.380 --> 10:08.620
♪♪

10:08.620 --> 10:09.620
[ Door opens ]

10:09.620 --> 10:11.540
Hi, Greg.
Thanks for meeting us.

10:11.540 --> 10:13.120
Lonnie, this is the writer
I was telling you about.

10:13.120 --> 10:14.580
Hey,
nice to meet you.

10:14.580 --> 10:16.460
Nice to meet you, too.
I love your videos.

10:16.460 --> 10:17.960
Ah, so you know
what I'm all about?

10:17.960 --> 10:20.040
I think I do.

10:20.040 --> 10:20.880
[ Paintball gun fires ]
Aah!

10:20.880 --> 10:23.120
Lonnie!

10:23.120 --> 10:24.710
What the hell was that?!

10:24.710 --> 10:27.540
I'm trying to have
a professional meeting,

10:27.540 --> 10:28.830
and you shoot me?!

10:28.830 --> 10:31.040
It was a prank to show
that we can, you know, vibe.

10:31.040 --> 10:33.120
That's not cool, bro!

10:33.120 --> 10:35.790
Angela,
I'll talk to you later.

10:35.790 --> 10:37.250
[ Door opens ]

10:37.250 --> 10:38.420
What the [bleep]
is wrong with you?

10:38.420 --> 10:39.960
Trip said he'd love it!

10:41.120 --> 10:42.540
I heard it.
I heard it.

10:42.540 --> 10:48.170
♪♪

10:48.170 --> 10:50.420
I can't believe you threw away
our company's future

10:50.420 --> 10:52.290
over something as dumb
as ingredients.

10:52.290 --> 10:54.790
You think
ingredients are dumb?

10:54.790 --> 10:57.460
Taste.

10:57.460 --> 10:59.330
I already know
what your lasagna tastes like.

10:59.330 --> 11:00.750
This isn't my lasagna.

11:00.750 --> 11:02.710
This is
Coastal Farms Lasagna,

11:02.710 --> 11:05.380
made with kelp noodles
and cashew cheese.

11:05.380 --> 11:07.210
You're finally
seeing things my way.

11:07.210 --> 11:08.000
Mm.

11:16.670 --> 11:18.040
Mmm.

11:20.170 --> 11:21.290
Not bad.

11:21.290 --> 11:23.790
[ Inhales sharply ]
Take another bite.

11:26.170 --> 11:27.250
[ Sighs ]
I can't.

11:27.250 --> 11:28.710
It's sludgy,
and it smells like the stuff

11:28.710 --> 11:30.460
the plumber pulled out
of the shower drain.

11:30.460 --> 11:32.880
Here is
some of the real lasagna

11:32.880 --> 11:34.250
to get that taste
out of your mouth.

11:38.000 --> 11:39.290
[ Sighs ]

11:41.670 --> 11:42.790
I'm sorry, Mom.

11:42.790 --> 11:45.120
You'd be crazy
to change the recipe.

11:45.120 --> 11:47.880
But we can't bring the good
stuff to Flavor of Westport.

11:47.880 --> 11:50.080
We should have just lied
and kept the recipe the same.

11:50.080 --> 11:51.960
We should have just lied!

11:51.960 --> 11:53.170
Now what are we gonna do?

11:55.670 --> 11:58.040
We could go down there
and secretly hand out samples

11:58.040 --> 11:59.580
at the festival
without a booth.

12:00.710 --> 12:03.290
I know I'm not supposed to
say stuff like this right now

12:03.290 --> 12:05.210
because you are
lying and cheating,

12:05.210 --> 12:07.290
but I have never been
more proud of you.

12:12.670 --> 12:15.080
These mason jars
were a great idea.

12:15.080 --> 12:16.880
Easy to secretly
hand out.

12:16.880 --> 12:18.580
Plus, they look fancy

12:18.580 --> 12:20.580
but are actually cheaper
than plastic containers

12:20.580 --> 12:21.920
and smaller.

12:21.920 --> 12:23.750
We can charge more
for less lasagna.

12:23.750 --> 12:24.960
It's a win-win.

12:24.960 --> 12:26.620
For us,
not the consumer.

12:26.620 --> 12:27.710
Which is another win.

12:27.710 --> 12:29.250
It's a win-win-win.

12:29.250 --> 12:30.670
I'm glad
you changed the name.

12:30.670 --> 12:33.210
"Mrs. O's Lasagna"
is a good compromise.

12:33.210 --> 12:35.460
This is nice,
us hanging out.

12:35.460 --> 12:36.830
Yeah, it is.

12:36.830 --> 12:40.210
We haven't spent this much time
together since...

12:40.210 --> 12:42.540
I was nursing you,
I suppose.

12:42.540 --> 12:45.170
We can use Taylor's college fund
for my therapy, right?

12:45.170 --> 12:46.380
[ Zipper closes ]

12:46.380 --> 12:49.080
♪♪

12:49.080 --> 12:50.750
No, it didn't go well.

12:50.750 --> 12:52.500
Lonnie stormed off.

12:52.500 --> 12:54.500
You must've done something
to make him angry.

12:54.500 --> 12:56.750
Did you start saying "hashtag"
in front of random sentences?

12:56.750 --> 12:58.120
That makes me angry.

12:58.120 --> 12:59.960
More likely it was me
shooting him at close range

12:59.960 --> 13:01.040
with a paintball gun.

13:01.040 --> 13:02.290
[ Both laugh ]

13:02.290 --> 13:03.790
See? That's funny.

13:03.790 --> 13:04.920
[ Eagle screeches ]

13:04.920 --> 13:06.500
And this is your idea
of babysitting?

13:06.500 --> 13:08.670
Leaving them
in front of the TV all weekend?

13:08.670 --> 13:10.250
Have they even eaten?

13:10.250 --> 13:12.290
Uh...

13:12.290 --> 13:14.250
I'm gonna go with
"possibly."

13:14.250 --> 13:16.880
That's the kind of thing
you should know.

13:16.880 --> 13:18.210
We've eaten, Mr. A.

13:19.460 --> 13:21.290
Your list says
"Get and keep a job."

13:21.290 --> 13:22.920
The way you're going,
that's not happening.

13:22.920 --> 13:24.080
[ Scoffs ] Fine!

13:24.080 --> 13:26.250
I'll do something fun
with them.

13:26.250 --> 13:28.380
[ Tribal music playing,
elephants trumpet ]

13:28.380 --> 13:29.670
[ Bird chirps ]

13:29.670 --> 13:31.080
[ Remote clicks ]

13:31.080 --> 13:32.080
What's happening?

13:32.080 --> 13:33.290
Where am I?

13:33.290 --> 13:34.670
Hey, guys.

13:34.670 --> 13:37.790
Since I'm an awesome babysitter,
we're gonna play a game.

13:37.790 --> 13:38.880
How about hide-and-seek?

13:38.880 --> 13:39.790
We'll hide first!

13:41.250 --> 13:42.460
One...

13:42.460 --> 13:43.460
two...

13:43.460 --> 13:44.880
No peeking!
...three...

13:44.880 --> 13:47.080
...four, five...

13:47.080 --> 13:50.620
six, seven, eight...

13:50.620 --> 13:55.830
♪♪

13:55.830 --> 14:01.420
♪♪

14:01.420 --> 14:03.880
[ Indistinct conversations ]

14:03.880 --> 14:04.880
Hey.

14:06.290 --> 14:08.250
You need lasagna?
I got the good stuff.

14:08.250 --> 14:09.670
I'll hook you up.

14:09.670 --> 14:11.080
First one's free.

14:12.500 --> 14:13.830
Psst. Try this.

14:13.830 --> 14:16.380
It's the real deal.
Pure mozzarella.

14:16.380 --> 14:17.790
Website's on the label.

14:17.790 --> 14:19.250
We were never here.

14:19.250 --> 14:23.580
♪♪

14:23.580 --> 14:26.040
How did you find me
in the bathtub?

14:26.040 --> 14:29.170
Well, for starters,
the shower curtain is clear.

14:29.170 --> 14:30.670
Also,
you were whistling.

14:30.670 --> 14:32.290
When you get "Eye Of The Tiger"
stuck in your head,

14:32.290 --> 14:34.080
it doesn't just go away
on its own.

14:34.080 --> 14:35.960
[ Scoffs ]

14:35.960 --> 14:38.710
[ Anna-Kat whistling
"Eye of the Tiger" ]

14:41.710 --> 14:43.170
Damn it, he's right.

14:43.170 --> 14:45.080
♪♪

14:45.080 --> 14:46.960
Franklin!

14:46.960 --> 14:48.670
We've looked everywhere.
Where is that kid?

14:48.670 --> 14:50.750
It's been two hours.
Franklin disappeared.

14:50.750 --> 14:52.170
Having fun, guys?

14:52.170 --> 14:53.460
Oh, yeah!

14:53.460 --> 14:55.540
We're having a great time
playing hide-and-seek.

14:55.540 --> 14:57.330
All four of us.
Good.

14:57.330 --> 14:59.040
Well, your mom called.

14:59.040 --> 15:01.290
I have to run
to Flavor of Westport.

15:01.290 --> 15:03.620
She sold someone
an entire lasagna.

15:03.620 --> 15:06.670
You really pulled this together.
I'm proud of you, Taylor.

15:06.670 --> 15:07.960
[ Door opens, closes ]

15:07.960 --> 15:09.750
We have to find Franklin.

15:09.750 --> 15:11.330
Franklin!

15:11.330 --> 15:13.420
Game's over!
You won!

15:13.420 --> 15:15.040
He's not coming out
until you find him.

15:15.040 --> 15:16.920
He takes these games
really seriously.

15:16.920 --> 15:18.830
He's technically
still in a game of tag

15:18.830 --> 15:20.500
with his cousins
from last Thanksgiving.

15:20.500 --> 15:23.920
♪♪

15:23.920 --> 15:25.580
Katie,
here's your lasagna.

15:25.580 --> 15:28.250
Put it on the bench,
don't look at me, and walk away.

15:28.250 --> 15:29.710
Sure. Of course.

15:29.710 --> 15:32.540
I would never assume I was just
gonna openly hand you lasagna,

15:32.540 --> 15:34.380
kiss you on the cheek, and say
"See you at home, honey."

15:34.380 --> 15:36.290
[ Whispering ]
Keep it moving.
Okay.

15:36.290 --> 15:42.250
♪♪

15:42.250 --> 15:48.170
♪♪

15:48.170 --> 15:50.120
Alright,
find Franklin.

15:51.750 --> 15:53.210
Show us where he is,
boy.

15:53.210 --> 16:00.540
♪♪

16:00.540 --> 16:02.960
Did you guys really think
that would work?

16:02.960 --> 16:04.120
Yeah.
Yeah.

16:04.120 --> 16:05.830
If you two get married,

16:05.830 --> 16:08.540
you should think strongly
about adopting.

16:08.540 --> 16:10.920
Well, what are we gonna do?
Franklin is nowhere to be found.

16:10.920 --> 16:12.500
You've got to call Dad
for help.

16:12.500 --> 16:13.920
But Dad's gonna be
so mad!

16:13.920 --> 16:15.500
He's not gonna
cross this off my list,

16:15.500 --> 16:16.500
he's gonna
take away my phone,

16:16.500 --> 16:17.790
he's not gonna let me
have dessert --

16:17.790 --> 16:20.920
A child is missing.

16:20.920 --> 16:22.250
Right.

16:22.250 --> 16:23.540
Right, right.

16:23.540 --> 16:25.040
♪♪

16:25.040 --> 16:26.960
Mmm. Mmm.

16:26.960 --> 16:31.710
♪♪

16:34.500 --> 16:36.670
[ Whispering ] Cops, cops, cops!
Act casual.

16:36.670 --> 16:43.380
♪♪

16:43.380 --> 16:44.620
[ Sighs ]

16:44.620 --> 16:46.670
We have got to get out of here
before we get busted.

16:46.670 --> 16:49.170
I hope we get busted.
I've never felt more alive.

16:50.540 --> 16:53.620
[ Cellphone ringing ]

16:53.620 --> 16:55.040
Police officer:
Greg Otto!

16:55.040 --> 16:56.670
Get on the ground with
your hands behind your head!

16:56.670 --> 16:58.120
Wait! What have I --
On the ground! Now!

16:58.120 --> 16:59.290
[ Grunts ]

16:59.290 --> 17:01.290
Greg Otto,
you're under arrest for assault.

17:01.290 --> 17:04.460
Lonnie Spears is
pressing charges for
your paintball attack.

17:04.460 --> 17:06.830
What? That was --
That was just a prank!

17:06.830 --> 17:09.420
I mean, please!
I have children!

17:09.420 --> 17:12.460
I'm sorry. I'm s--
[ Laughing ] I'm sorry.

17:12.460 --> 17:13.750
I don't understand.

17:13.750 --> 17:15.540
You're not
going to jail.

17:15.540 --> 17:16.540
These guys
are actors.

17:16.540 --> 17:18.080
You should see
your face, dude.

17:18.080 --> 17:19.500
You look like
my friend's dad

17:19.500 --> 17:21.330
when he got nabbed
on "To Catch a Predator."

17:21.330 --> 17:22.880
W-Why would you
do this?

17:22.880 --> 17:24.210
Because it's funny.

17:24.210 --> 17:25.330
[ Laughs ]

17:25.330 --> 17:26.790
And Angela came to me
and pled your case,

17:26.790 --> 17:28.000
so you should
really thank her.

17:28.000 --> 17:29.670
She gave me your book
on John Stuart Mill,

17:29.670 --> 17:30.750
and I read it
last night.

17:30.750 --> 17:31.750
You did?
Yeah.

17:31.750 --> 17:32.790
Loved it.

17:32.790 --> 17:34.420
You're exactly
the kind of ghostwriter

17:34.420 --> 17:35.790
I need for my memoir.

17:35.790 --> 17:38.330
You can give my life story
the emotional gravitas it needs.

17:38.330 --> 17:39.670
So the job is yours.

17:39.670 --> 17:41.210
[ Exhales sharply ]
Great.

17:41.210 --> 17:42.960
Can -- Can they take off
the handcuffs now?

17:42.960 --> 17:44.330
Oh, not yet.

17:44.330 --> 17:47.170
One more thing,
and this is important --

17:47.170 --> 17:48.540
I'm the one
who does the pranks.

17:48.540 --> 17:49.540
Not you.

17:49.540 --> 17:50.540
[ Paintball gun fires ]

17:50.540 --> 17:53.040
Ow!
[ Laughing ]
I'm sorry!

17:53.040 --> 17:54.540
Sorry!
[ Paintball gun fires ]

17:54.540 --> 17:56.380
Aah!
Mm, man,
we're gonna have fun!

17:56.380 --> 17:57.960
So much fun, dude.

17:57.960 --> 18:00.920
This is exactly why I spent
all those years getting a Ph.D.

18:00.920 --> 18:02.620
[ Laughs ]
Oh, yeah, dude.
[ Laughs ]

18:02.620 --> 18:04.080
Let's track down
Mom or Dad

18:04.080 --> 18:05.750
so they can help us
find Franklin.

18:05.750 --> 18:07.620
Hey, there's Franklin.
Maybe he's seen your parents.

18:08.830 --> 18:10.290
Franklin! Thank God!

18:11.620 --> 18:13.620
How did you end up here?

18:13.620 --> 18:16.000
I hid under a blanket in
the back seat of your dad's car.

18:16.000 --> 18:18.000
And it was so cozy,
I just fell asleep.

18:18.000 --> 18:20.250
And when I woke up,
I was here.

18:20.250 --> 18:22.420
I'm just happy
you're safe.

18:22.420 --> 18:24.330
Hi, Mr. Otto.

18:24.330 --> 18:26.330
Well,
hey, guys.

18:26.330 --> 18:28.080
Taylor's the best babysitter
I've ever had.

18:28.080 --> 18:29.500
Oh, I'm glad
to hear it.

18:29.500 --> 18:30.750
You can check that
off your list, Taylor.

18:30.750 --> 18:32.080
What happened
to your shirt?

18:32.080 --> 18:33.620
Lonnie Spears
shot me.

18:33.620 --> 18:34.920
It's going to
bruise.

18:34.920 --> 18:36.620
But thanks to you and Franklin,
I got the job.

18:36.620 --> 18:38.540
You're going to need
that extra income.

18:38.540 --> 18:40.580
I also ordered you
a gazebo.

18:40.580 --> 18:42.380
It's going to look great
with the fruit trees,

18:42.380 --> 18:43.710
but it was not cheap.

18:43.710 --> 18:49.380
♪♪

18:49.380 --> 18:51.960
Are you seeing
all the orders that rolled in?

18:51.960 --> 18:52.960
Yeah!

18:52.960 --> 18:54.620
Congratulations, Mom.

18:54.620 --> 18:56.540
Your hobby's on its way
to becoming a real business.

18:56.540 --> 18:58.540
Well...

18:58.540 --> 19:00.960
I couldn't have done any of this
without your help.

19:00.960 --> 19:02.750
That's true.

19:02.750 --> 19:04.460
And now that
I've proven my worth,

19:04.460 --> 19:06.330
I was thinking it might be time
to renegotiate

19:06.330 --> 19:08.540
my ownership stake
in the company.

19:08.540 --> 19:09.920
Absolutely.

19:09.920 --> 19:12.250
How about on three,
we both say a number?

19:12.250 --> 19:14.210
Okay, one --

19:15.710 --> 19:16.880
[ Door closes ]

19:16.880 --> 19:23.040
♪♪

19:23.040 --> 19:24.880
Good news -- one of the guys
we gave a sample to

19:24.880 --> 19:26.210
is a member
of the Elks Club.

19:26.210 --> 19:28.120
They want seven lasagnas
for their next meeting.

19:28.120 --> 19:29.250
Amazing!

19:29.250 --> 19:30.620
We better get cooking.

19:30.620 --> 19:32.960
So, you gonna teach me
your secret recipe?
No.

19:32.960 --> 19:34.330
If I told you,
you would steal it

19:34.330 --> 19:35.920
and start
a competing company.

19:35.920 --> 19:37.670
Aw, Mom.
You get me.

19:37.670 --> 19:39.210
But you can help.

19:39.210 --> 19:42.420
We start with
a 13x10 baking dish,

19:42.420 --> 19:43.420
which we keep down here.

19:44.790 --> 19:46.080
What the hell?!

19:46.080 --> 19:47.080
Trip?!

19:47.080 --> 19:48.250
How did you --

19:48.250 --> 19:49.880
Anna-Kat: He's got to
be here someplace!

19:49.880 --> 19:51.580
[ Footsteps in distance ]
Shhhhhh.

19:57.460 --> 19:59.920
[ Trip whistling
"Eye of the Tiger" ]

20:03.620 --> 20:04.620
[ Whirring ]

20:04.620 --> 20:05.710
What is this?

20:05.710 --> 20:07.040
Are you Greg Otto?
Yeah.

20:07.040 --> 20:08.040
Your gazebo's here.

20:08.040 --> 20:09.080
This is a mistake.

20:09.080 --> 20:10.420
My daughter's friend
ordered this.

20:10.420 --> 20:12.040
Can you take it back?
No.

20:12.040 --> 20:13.500
Can you at least
put it in the backyard?

20:13.500 --> 20:14.750
We're not allowed
to do that.

20:14.750 --> 20:17.040
[ Brakes squeak ]

20:17.040 --> 20:18.540
Are you Greg Otto?
Yeah.

20:18.540 --> 20:19.920
I have
your fruit trees.

20:19.920 --> 20:21.250
I-I didn't order these.

20:21.250 --> 20:22.960
Can you take them back?
No.

20:22.960 --> 20:24.790
[ Sighs ]
Okay, well,

20:24.790 --> 20:26.750
I guess you can
put them in the backyard.

20:26.750 --> 20:28.170
I'm not allowed
to do that.

20:28.170 --> 20:29.500
You're just gonna
leave them here?

20:29.500 --> 20:30.620
You're not
gonna plant them?

20:30.620 --> 20:32.540
You can't plant these
until spring.

20:32.540 --> 20:34.250
Well, what am I gonna do
with fruit trees in the winter?

20:34.250 --> 20:35.540
I'm not the one
who ordered them.

20:35.540 --> 20:37.120
I didn't order them,
either!

20:37.120 --> 20:38.210
You Greg Otto?

20:38.210 --> 20:39.420
No!

20:39.420 --> 20:41.330
[ Llama groans ]

20:45.000 --> 20:49.500
♪♪
